"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754832","Home Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Information on processing times for applications for leave to remain is published quarterly in the Home Office’s temporary and permanent migration statistics.</p><p> </p><p>A link to the most recent available data is available at;</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/temporary-and-permanent-migration-data-february-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/temporary-and-permanent-migration-data-february-2017</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-11T14:30:39.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754832/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754832/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-20","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for leave to remain did not meet her Department's service standard processing time in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17; and how many such applications took more than a year to process in each period.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","6434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754833","Home Office","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Violence Against Women and Girls Inter Ministerial Group has met once since they met on 13 October 2016.</p><p> </p><p>This meeting took place on 2 March 2017, where Ministers heard directly from VAWG charity representatives about how best to prioritise Government efforts to tackle VAWG.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-05T08:07:45.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754833/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754833/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-20","Violence against Women and Girls Ministerial Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many times and on which dates the Inter-Ministerial Group on Violence Against Women and Girls has met since 13 October 2016.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754834","Home Office","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Home Office does not hold the data in the format requested. This data is not held centrally and to obtain it would therefore exceed the disproportionate cost threshold.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-05T08:08:33.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754834/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754834/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-20","Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what compensation payments her Department has made at the request of the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Naz Shah","Bradford West","Naz Shah","6445"
