"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753977","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-05","<p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</a></p><p> </p><p>Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a></p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-09-05T13:40:11.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753977/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753977/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-19","Cabinet Office: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what research his Department has commissioned from The Hay Group; and of what value those contracts are.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","6326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753978","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-07","<p>The government fully supports the principles of better debt management and lower levels of problem debt. This government has a manifesto commitment to introduce a statutory breathing space that would give heavily indebted consumers a period of respite from enforcement action, and further interest and charges for a period of up to six weeks. Where appropriate, they will be offered a statutory repayment plan to help them pay back their debts in a sustainable way. We will outline further information on how this policy could be implemented in due course.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-09-07T16:10:49.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753978/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753978/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-19","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effect that a statutory breathing space for indebted households would have on alleviating problem debt and bankruptcy.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","6279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753979","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-05","<p>Departments are responsible for collecting relevant data for the workforces in their areas and it would be for them to confirm the precise data.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-09-05T12:53:47.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753979/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753979/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-19","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what information his Department holds on the proportion of public sector employees who are (a) at the top of their relevant pay scale or (b) did not receive progression pay for any other reason in the most recent financial year for which data exists.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","6319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753980","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-07","<p>The criteria for enhanced annuities on the grounds of ill health are set by individual pension providers in the terms and conditions of individual policies. Consumers should check with pension providers whether they are eligible for an enhanced annuity. As the Financial Conduct Authority’s recently published Retirement Outcomes Review interim report noted, over 90% of all enhanced annuities are purchased on the open market and consumers should shop around for the best possible deal.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","6015","2017-09-07T15:50:15.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753980/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753980/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-19","Annuities: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to alter the criteria for claiming an enhanced annuity on the grounds of ill health.","false","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter","6253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753981","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-06","<p>In line with commitments in the UK Aid Strategy, the government has introduced robust monitoring, governance and oversight arrangements to ensure value for money of all Official Development Assistance (ODA) spend, including through setting up an ODA Senior Officials Group which reports to Ministers.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-09-06T13:40:41.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753981/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753981/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-19","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to improve oversight of the UK aid strategy across government; and what steps he has taken in response to the National Audit Office recommended in its report on Managing the Official Development Assistance Target that his Department should improve its cross-government analysis of the effect of ODA expenditure.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","6257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753982","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-05","<p>Data on outstanding challenges against the 2010 rating lists in England and Wales, and the 2017 rating lists in Wales, is publicly available at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/non-domestic-rating-challenges-and-changes-england-and-wales-june-2017-non-check-challenge-and-appeal-cca</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-05T07:54:29.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753982/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753982/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-19","Non-domestic Rates: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the current number of outstanding business rate appeals lodged with the valuation office is.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","6237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753983","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-06","<p>In March 2017, Professor Russel Griggs was appointed as the Independent Reviewer of HBOS Reading customer compensation cases by Lloyds Banking Group (LBG), in consultation with the Financial Conduct Authority. His appointment is therefore not a matter for government. The government expects that the appointment of Professor Griggs will help LBG to resolve outstanding cases as soon as possible, so that any victims of fraud at HBOS Reading can be properly compensated.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","6144 ; 6145 ; 6146","2017-09-06T10:09:00.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753983/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753983/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-19","Russel Griggs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has received on the appointment of Professor Russell Griggs as the independent reviewer of HBOS Reading fraud cases.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","6143"
